argin-bottom:0;\">If you&#8217;re unsure, the top-rated pick is the lower-risk choice; the budget pick is reasonable if price is your primary constraint.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin:24px 0;\">\n<h3 style=\"margin-top:0;\">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">How much storage should I get for an iPad?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">64-128GB suits typical use (apps, photos, streaming with some downloads); 256GB or more is worth it if you shoot a lot of video, work with large creative files, or plan to keep the device for many years without cloud reliance.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Do I need to pay extra for cellular connectivity, or is Wi-Fi enough?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Wi-Fi-only models are cheaper and cover home/office use fine; cellular models add ongoing data plan costs but let you get online anywhere without relying on a hotspot - worth it mainly if you need connectivity away from Wi-Fi regularly.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Which iPad models support Apple Pencil, and does it matter which generation?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Apple Pencil support and which generation (1st or 2nd) is compatible varies by iPad model - check the specific model’s compatibility before buying a pencil separately, since older and newer iPads don’t all support the same generation.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">How many years of software updates can I expect?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">iPads generally receive a long run of major software updates compared to most Android tablets, often five or more years from release - though the exact number varies by model generation and Apple’s current support policy at time of purchase.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
